  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "E-learning has become widely used in classrooms and has played a crucial role in today's learning, particularly with the rise of Massive Open Online Courses (MOOCs) and ondemand learning (Aboagye et al., 2021; Maatuk et al., 2022), especially in response to the COVID-19 pandemic.",
    "One prominent type of e-learning is Intelligent Tutoring Systems (ITS), which aims to provide learners with immediate and personalized instruction or feedback.",
    "ITS uses an approach from the Vygotskian, i.e., Zone of Proximal Development theory (Reber, 1995), to provide each student with tasks that are of appropriate difficulty.",
    "According to this theory, students develop their skills and knowledge in situations where tasks cannot be solved by the student alone but can be solved with the help of an expert, known as scaffolding.",
    "Inappropriate task difficulty can lead to minimal progress and result in negative affect such as boredom or frustration (Fenza et al., 2017)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "E-learning has become widely used in classrooms and has played a crucial role in today's learning, particularly with the rise of Massive Open Online Courses (MOOCs) and ondemand learning (Aboagye et al., 2021; Maatuk et al., 2022), especially in response to the COVID-19 pandemic.",
    "ITS uses an approach from the Vygotskian, i.e., Zone of Proximal Development theory (Reber, 1995), to provide each student with tasks that are of appropriate difficulty.",
    "Inappropriate task difficulty can lead to minimal progress and result in negative affect such as boredom or frustration (Fenza et al., 2017)."
  ]
